data.name: InfoPic.ToolTip
data.value:
Kind of a work in progress, but should give you a little help in finding out if a loadbank can get the current that you need at a certain voltage.
Should be tooltips for most things.
any issues, improvements or slaggings, gimme a shout and ill promptly ignore them here : dmcbain@norcoenergy.com
Basic use : Select a loadbank to use, enter a string ETV voltage then click the Show achievable current.
Advanced Use : select loadbank to use. click 'define string' to create a battery string with a selectable type and cell/block count. ETV voltage will be automagically calculated based on created string. enter the discharge rate required for testing. then click Show Achievable, to get further information
